\begin{abstract}
A review of the approximations in any time-depedendent
density functional calculation of excitation energies is
given.   The single-pole approximation for the susceptibility
is used to understand errors in popular approximations for
the exchange-correlation kernel.  A new hybrid of exact
exchange and adiabatic local density approximation is proposed
and tested on the He and Be atoms.
\end{abstract}
